          p.content-normal(style="color:#fbfbfb") I am Venezuelan-born and have two nationalities: Venezuelan and Spanish (I like to think I am a mix of the best parts of both cultures.) I am a family man, happily married now for twenty-nine years to María de los Ángeles, a beautiful and exceptional woman in every sense, both inside and out. I have three children who are genuinely out of this world for how fantastic and extraordinary they are: twenty-four years old Oliver, twenty-one years old Oriana, and our youngest, Aaron who is sixteen.

          p.content-normal(style="color:#fbfbfb") Thanks to my profession, I have lived in three different countries, I have had the opportunity to travel half the world; which has allowed me to meet and nurture from different cultures as well as hundreds of people whom I have learned, among many things, that at the end we are all the same, we all face the same problems, suffer for the same reasons, want the same things in life and fear pretty much the same things.

          p.content-normal(style="color:#fbfbfb")  I consider myself a promoter of the importance of having a positive attitude in life (this is what my book is all about) and how can this one be is the main means of achieving the much desired happiness and in the worst case, allowing you to be fine in spite of the circumstances.

          p.content-normal(style="color:#fbfbfb")  I believe in family, moral values, that 2 plus 2 will always be equal four and that we should never stop laughing. I also believe in taking care of one self, I exercise every day (running & Gym) and I always busy with a personal project and my hobbies includes: flying RC plane models, writing, photographic and graphology. But, above all these there is no doubt in my mind that the moments I enjoy the most are the ones I spend with my family.


